To reproduce any panel you need the Clinical data which is only available from the corresponding author upon reasonable request.

  • Annotating TLS-associated spots: Spatial spots belonging to TLS were defined by CD3/CD20 staining on the consecutive slide for frozen tumours or on the sample block for FFPE tumours, then we manually annotated using Loupe Browser (10X genomics). A tutorial can be found in Introduction to Spatial Transcriptomic Data Analysis - A Case Study of Renal carcinoma. The TLS annotation of each slide can be found in the GEO under the name âTLS_annotation.csvâ. -

  • Annotating TLS-adjacent spots: A quick function to annotate TLS-adjacent spots using a Seurat object can be done by charging the object âAdjacent_spot_annotation.rdsâ

#Use meta_all to perform differential abundance analysis between Responders and non-Responders in the TLS and each TLS-adjacent spot

slide_list_TLS_2<-slides_id[c(1:8,10:18)]#Take out P_19 #Low number of TLS-associated spots that was not used for the integration for panel c-f
meta_all_2<-meta_all[meta_all$Sample!="P_19",]

Res_FC_all<-data.frame()
signs_to_test<-sigs_starfysh
for (name_adjacent in c("TLS","Adjacent_TLS_1order", "Adjacent_TLS_2order", "Adjacent_TLS_3order", "Adjacent_TLS_4order","Adjacent_TLS_5order", "Adjacent_TLS_6order", "Adjacent_TLS_7order", "Adjacent_TLS_8order")) {
  print(name_adjacent)
 ###Subset 
meta_subset<-subset(meta_all_2,Adjacent_TLS_8_levels_combined==name_adjacent)
#Subset samples just in case
meta_subset<-subset(meta_subset,Sample%in%slide_list_TLS_2)
 
###DEanalys for signatures/pops
library(sjmisc)
t<-melt(meta_subset,id.vars=c("RECIST_R_nR","Sample"), measure.vars=signs_to_test)

pairwise.test <- t %>% mutate(variable2 = variable) %>% group_by(variable2) %>% rstatix::wilcox_test(value ~ RECIST_R_nR)
 ##Calculate log2FC to add
log2FC<-meta_subset%>%
    group_by(RECIST_R_nR,vars(signs_to_test))%>%
    summarise_at(vars(signs_to_test), mean, na.rm = TRUE) %>%
    dplyr::select(-`vars(signs_to_test)`)%>% 
    rotate_df(cn=T)%>% 
    filter(!row_number() %in% c(1))%>% #Eliminate first row
    mutate(log2FC=log2(as.numeric(NR)/as.numeric(R)))
###Add to pvalues
pairwise.test$log2FC<-log2FC$log2FC[pairwise.test$variable2]
#Add means
pairwise.test$Mean_NR<-log2FC$NR[pairwise.test$variable2]
pairwise.test$Mean_R<-log2FC$R[pairwise.test$variable2]
#Adjust pval
pairwise.test$p.adj<-p.adjust(pairwise.test$p,method = "BH")
pairwise.test<-as.data.frame(pairwise.test)  
pairwise.test$variable2<-as.character(pairwise.test$variable2)
###Merge genes and signatures...
Final_testing<-data.frame(variable=c(pairwise.test$variable2),avg_log2FC=c(pairwise.test$log2FC),
                          Mean_NR=pairwise.test$Mean_NR,Mean_R=pairwise.test$Mean_R,
                          p=c(pairwise.test$p),p.adj=c(pairwise.test$p.adj),TLS_number=name_adjacent)
#View(Final_testing[Final_testing$p.adj<0.05,])

##Merge with previous results
Res_FC_all<-rbind(Res_FC_all,Final_testing)

}
##Save final matrix
saveRDS(Res_FC_all,file = "Res_FC_all.rds")

#########Plot
to_plot_log2<-c("ccRCC_PT_like_starfysh","ccRCC_p53_EMT_starfysh","ccRCC_Proflammatory_like_starfysh","ccRCC_PI3K_starfysh") #Change names accordingly

Res_FC_all2<-Res_FC_all

Res_FC_all3$variable<-factor(Res_FC_all3$variable,levels = c(to_plot_log2[1],to_plot_log2[2],to_plot_log2[3],to_plot_log2[4]))
Res_FC_all3$TLS_number<-factor(Res_FC_all3$TLS_number,levels = c("TLS","Adjacent_TLS_1order", "Adjacent_TLS_2order", "Adjacent_TLS_3order", "Adjacent_TLS_4order" ,"Adjacent_TLS_5order", "Adjacent_TLS_6order","Adjacent_TLS_7order" ,"Adjacent_TLS_8order"))
#ggplot(df3, aes(x=dose, y=len, group = supp, shape=supp, linetype=supp))

Res_FC_all3$p_format<-Res_FC_all3$p.adj %>% 
  rstatix::p_format(digits = 2) %>% 
  rstatix::p_mark_significant()
Res_FC_all3$p_format<-gsub("^[^*]+","",Res_FC_all3$p_format) #Only keep *
Res_FC_all3$p_format[nchar(Res_FC_all3$p_format)==0]<-"ns"

#The plot

                             group=variable,

)) +geom_line(size=1.5) + geom_point(size=4)+ scale_color_manual(values=c("firebrick1",'#999999',"dodgerblue","tan1"))+theme_std()+theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1))+ggtitle("Log2FC NR vs R")+ylab("Average Log2FC")+xlab("Distance from TLS (spot number)")+
geom_text(label = Res_FC_all3$p_format, x = Res_FC_all3$TLS_number, y = Res_FC_all3$avg_log2FC,vjust = -1, hjust = 0, nudge_x = -0.45,size = 7)

library(Seurat)
library(SCP)


##############Second integrate in a unique Seurat object all the TLS spots for both R (n=8) and NR (n=9) ############"
###Now lets subset for each sample to the tumoral cells and use SCTtransform to use regularised negative binomial regression to normalise UMI counts 
TLS_spatial_integrated<-list()
slides_id<-paste0("P_",seq(01,19,by=1)) #
slide_list_TLS_2<-slides_id[c(1:8,10:18)]#Take out P_19 #Low number of TLS-associated spots that was not used for the integration for panel c-f

nfeatures<-56000 ###This is the number of features to return after normalization, we need all

for (y in slide_list_TLS) {
  tmp_name<-y
  print(tmp_name)
  file.tmp<-paste0("MyoutsPath","/",tmp_name) #This must be the path were you stored the Seurat object
  setwd(file.tmp)
  
Seurat_obj<-readRDS(file = paste0("Seurat_obj_",tmp_name,".rds"))

###Subset to TLS spots
Subset <- subset(x = Seurat_obj, cells = rownames(Seurat_obj@meta.data)[Seurat_obj$TLS_annotation_updated=="TLS"])
cat("Number of TLS spots is",(ncol(Subset)))

###SCTransform...with the percentage of mitochondria genes being regressed out
Subset <- SCTransform(Subset, verbose = T, 
                                    variable.features.n = nfeatures,assay = "Spatial")

TLS_spatial_integrated[[tmp_name]]<-Subset
  
rm(Seurat_obj)
gc()
setwd("MyoutsPath")

}
print("FindIntegrationAnchors")



nfeatures<-2000 ##Change to 2000
features <- SelectIntegrationFeatures(object.list = TLS_spatial_integrated, 
                                          nfeatures = nfeatures)

print(length(features)) 

TLS_spatial_integrated <- PrepSCTIntegration(object.list = TLS_spatial_integrated, 
                                  anchor.features = features, verbose = T)

 dr_dim.use = 1:50; selection.method = "vst";max.features = 200; k.score = 12; k.filter = NA; integration_dims = 1:12;
 ##Here we used 10 dimensions for integrating since there is a sample containing only 13 spots
 #Decrease the k.filter or eliminate it
 
anchors <- FindIntegrationAnchors(object.list = TLS_spatial_integrated, 
                                      normalization.method = "SCT", anchor.features = features, 
                                      verbose = T, max.features = max.features, k.score = k.score, 
                                      k.filter = k.filter, dims = integration_dims) 

TLS_spatial_integrated_final = IntegrateData(anchorset = anchors,
                               normalization.method = "SCT",dims = 1:30,
                               verbose = T,k.weight=12)

DefaultAssay(TLS_spatial_integrated_final) <- "integrated"
saveRDS(TLS_spatial_integrated_final,"TLS_spatial_integrated_final.rds")

##No longer needed objects...remove to make space
rm(anchors,TLS_spatial_integrated)
gc()

###Add responder data....

TLS_spatial_integrated_final$RECIST_R_nR<-Clinical_dat$RECIST_R_nR[match(TLS_spatial_integrated_final$Sample,Clinical_dat$Sample)] #Only possible upon request



# Run the standard workflow for visualization and clustering on the integrated assay
  print("ScaleData on the integrated Assay")
TLS_spatial_integrated_final <- ScaleData(TLS_spatial_integrated_final, verbose = T)
  print("RunPCA")
  dr_dim.use<-1:30
  TLS_spatial_integrated_final <- RunPCA(object = TLS_spatial_integrated_final, npcs = 30, 
                       verbose = T)
  dims.use = dr_dim.use
##Get significant PCAs
  
####Now perform the UMAP with these significant dimensions.....    
 print("RunUMAP")
  TLS_spatial_integrated_final <- RunUMAP(TLS_spatial_integrated_final, dims = dims.use)   

###Find neighboors
TLS_spatial_integrated_final <- FindNeighbors(object = TLS_spatial_integrated_final, dims = dims.use)

TLS_spatial_integrated_final <- FindClusters(object = TLS_spatial_integrated_final, resolution = 0.3)
  

##Plot... panel c 
library(SCP)
CellDimPlot(
  srt = TLS_spatial_integrated_final, group.by = c("RECIST_R_nR"),
  reduction = "UMAP",pt.size = 1,palcolor = list(c("#09C1C6","#F98982")))
